	   <tr><td colspan=2>I thought this was funny as hell and congrats on the win, but I'm concerned about a fellow bard who could be at lvl 22 and not be familiar with (or at least not practicing) twisted songs. I'm only lvl 13 (as of this writing) and I twist like a wild man! (if I were a man) I can solo mobs who con yellow due to twisting. it makes up for the slow process of lvling when you can get more exp at once. Just let out a bellow and then twist in anthem, lather rinse repeat...it's a beautiful combo at my lvl because once the mob begins to turn tail and run, I switch to my restoration song and heal while I finnish em off which allows me shorter downtime (heal time). I don't know that this process (for my lvl) is common practice, but it's punk rock glory.<br>&nbsp;<br>~Serotonin~<br>Punk Rock Diva of the 27th Song</td></tr>
